<p>Vehicles transporting the South Korean delegation, led by South 
Korean Unification Ministrer Cho Myoung-Gyon, drive past a checkpoint on
 the road connecting South and North Korea at the Unification Bridge, 
near the Demilitarized zone (DMZ) separating them both on January 9, 
2018 in Paju. They began their first official face-to-face talks in two 
years.</p>
