<p class="rm-manual">“It is of remarkable historic significance that Kim
 Jong-un, the great leader of our revolution who opens up the period of a
 great leap for the development of the revolution, personally left the 
sacred trace in the revolutionary battle sites in [the] Mount Paektu 
area, the source of the lifeline of the revolution and inexhaustible 
patriotism, through knee-high virgin snow,” KCNA reported.</p>
<p class="rm-manual">Mr Kim said his tour had “hardened his resolution to defend the gains of the revolution”.</p>
<p class="rm-manual">He said Korean people needed to have a proper 
understanding of the “revolutionary traditions” of Mount Paektu, and 
claimed this would help them “demonstrate the country’s dignity and 
honour before the world”.</p>
<p class="rm-manual">This spirit, he added, would enable them to 
overcome “the unprecedented blockade and pressure imposed by the 
imperialists,” and help them “get prepared for the harshness and 
protracted character of our revolution”.</p>
